❓ Observability Design (Interview Answer – SRE Style)

I would design observability using metrics, logs, and traces (3 pillars) with a centralized stack like Prometheus + Grafana + Loki/ELK + OpenTelemetry + Alertmanager.

1️⃣ Metrics, Logs, Traces Collection
Metrics: Use Prometheus to scrape Kubernetes metrics (pods, nodes, app metrics via exporters).
Logs: Use FluentBit/Fluentd to ship container logs to Loki or ELK.
Traces: Use OpenTelemetry SDK to collect distributed traces and send to Jaeger/Tempo.
2️⃣ Dashboards & Alerts
Grafana dashboards for latency, error rate, traffic, CPU/memory, queue depth.
Alertmanager for alerting based on SLO/SLA thresholds (like 5xx rate, high latency, pod restarts).
Define alerts based on symptoms not causes.
3️⃣ Scalability, Cost & Security
Use namespace-based scraping + label filtering to reduce noise and cost.
Store logs with retention policies and compression.
Secure with RBAC, IAM roles, TLS encryption, and secret management (Vault/KMS).
Use sampling for traces to control cost.
4️⃣ Health Checks & SLI/SLO
Kubernetes liveness/readiness probes for service health.
Define SLIs like availability, latency, error rate.
SLOs like “99.9% successful requests in 5 min window” with burn-rate alerts.
